  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has already initiated restitution. While embezzlement is a breach of fiduciary trust, the court finds that a lengthy prison sentence would be disproportionate. The emotional outbursts from the public gallery are irrelevant to the legal merits of the case. Considering the circumstances and the need for both punishment and rehabilitation, a sentence of 6 months is appropriate to maintain public integrity without imposing an overly punitive measure on a non-violent, first-time offender.",
  "verdict": 6
